<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hi, I&#39;m making the switch from <strong>Neovim</strong> to <strong>Emacs</strong> for <strong>Clojure</strong> development.</p> <p>For the completion I&#39;m used to <code>&lt;Tab&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;S-Tab&gt;</code> for cycling through suggestions, and the suggestions would be automatically placed in the buffer when selected so that <code>&lt;Enter&gt;</code> would only behave as a newline.</p> <p>This is what I got for now:</p> <p><code>elisp (use-package company :init (add-hook &#39;after-init-hook &#39;global-company-mode) :config (global-company-mode t) (setq company-minimum-prefix-length 1) (setq company-idle-delay 0.0) :bind (:map company-active-map (&quot;TAB&quot; . company-select-next) (&quot;&lt;backtab&gt;&quot; . company-select-previous) (&quot;RET&quot; . nil))) </code></p> <p>Issues:</p> <ol> <li>Now I don&#39;t have a way to autocomplete since when I select suggestions they don&#39;t get placed in the buffer</li> <li>Placing <code>S-TAB</code> instead of <code>&lt;backtab&gt;</code> in the <code>:bind</code> section doesn&#39;t work</li> <li>If I tap <code>&lt;S-Tab&gt;</code>, then pressing <code>&lt;Enter&gt;</code> becomes unresponsive</li> </ol> <p>Thanks! Any help is appreciated. :D (Also if you see some bad practice tell me please)</p> <p>EDIT: did I do something wrong? I see a 50% of downvoting rate</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/sicr0"> /u/sicr0 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w2rd1o/trying_to_emulate_on_company_vim_behaviour/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w2rd1o/trying_to_emulate_on_company_vim_behaviour/">[comments]</a></span>